custom-dropdown-default.markDown:
"<h2>Custom dropdown default<span class="status refactor">Needs refactoring</span><span class="status js">JS</span></h2>

<p>If the options list in the select is too big, you might need an user-friendly scrollbar: just add <code>scrollable</code> attribute on <code>&lt;custom-dropdown&gt;</code> tag (see examples below).<br></p>
<p>If you want to use it in a react (or preact) project you might need to use <code>shouldComponentUpdate</code> method to avoid unexpected state changes.<br />Just add it as a method of you class:</p>
<p><code>shouldComponentUpdate() {
    return false;
}</code></p>
<p>More info &amp; examples here: <a href="https://preactjs.com/guide/external-dom-mutations">https://preactjs.com/guide/external-dom-mutations</a></p>
"

