google-map.markDown:
"<h2>Google Map<span class="status approved">Approved</span></h2>

<p>To use google map on your page add <code>as24-google-map</code> custom element on it. Please provide following data-attributes:<br><code>apikey</code> - your google public API key (visit <a href="https://console.developers.google.com/projectselector/apis/credentials" target="_blank">https://console.developers.google.com/projectselector/apis/credentials</a> if you need to generate it)<br><code>query</code> - location (e.g. <code>Dingolfinger Str. 1-15 81673 München</code> or <code>48.138570, 11.573496</code>)<br>You also have to provide height to make map interactive</p>
<pre><code class="lang-css">.sc-google-maps--example {
    height: 300px;
}
</code></pre>
<style>
#google-map .sc-google-maps {
    height: 300px;
}
</style>
"

